cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.ET

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper proposes an architectural technique for wear-leveling of non-volatile last level caches (LLCs).
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The proposed technique involves a software-controlled mapping layer between groups of physical pages and cache sets, which can be seen as a form of distributed computing.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses cache management policies and proposes a technique to improve the cache lifetime, which can be seen as a form of control.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The proposed technique involves a software-controlled mapping layer, which can be seen as a software engineering solution.
- cs.ET (Embedded Systems): The use of non-volatile devices such as STT-RAM for designing on-chip caches can be seen as an embedded systems application.
